U.K. Stocks Fluctuate as Admiral, Serco Fall; WPP Shares Advance in London

-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 
2011-08-24T08:13:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/u-k-stocks-fluctuate-as-admiral-serco-fall-wpp-shares-advance-in-london.html
U.K. stocks swung between gains and
losses, leaving the FTSE 100 Index little changed at 5,121.63 at
9:10 a.m. in  London .  The benchmark gauge has swung between gains at least five
times so far today amid speculation the Federal Reserve will act
to bolster the  U.S. economy .  Admiral Group Plc, Serco Group Plc and Diageo Plc paced
declining shares, all falling more than 3 percent. WPP Plc and
Tullow Oil Plc, helped limit losses on the FTSE 100, both
rallying more than 3 percent in London trading.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sarah Jones at 
 sjones35@bloomberg.net  